b.archive.org/web/20170908112857/https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=VC4lDwAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA159" id="mwBVI">Archived</a> from the original on 8 September 2017.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Managing+Diversity+in+Organizations%3A+A+Global+Perspective&amp;rft.pages=159&amp;rft.pub=Taylor+%26+Francis&amp;rft.date=2017&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-317-42368-3&amp;rft.aulast=Triana&amp;rft.aufirst=Mar%C3%ADa&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.uk%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DVC4lDwAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPA159&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AShia+Islam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt14" id="mwBVM"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt14" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwBVQ"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-4" id="cite_note-4"><a href="./Shia_Islam#cite_ref-4" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-4" class="mw-reference-text"><i id="mwBVU">Shi'a</i> is an alternative spelling of <i id="mwBVY">Shia</i>, and <i id="mwBVc">Shi'ite</i> of <i id="mwBVg">Shiite</i>. In subsequent sections, the spellings <i id="mwBVk">Shia</i> and <i id="mwBVo">Shiite</i> are adopted for consistency, except where the alternative spelling is in the title of a reference.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-PEW2009-5" id="cite_note-PEW2009-5"><a href="./Shia_Islam#cite_ref-PEW2009_5-0" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-PEW2009-5" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt19" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"title":{"wt":"Mapping the Global Muslim Population"},"url":{"wt":"http://www.pewforum.org/2009/10/07/mapping-the-global-muslim-population/"},"accessdate":{"wt":"10 December 2014"},"deadurl":{"wt":"no"},"archiveurl":{"wt":"https://web.archive.org/web/20151214172939/http://www.pewforum.org/2009/10/07/mapping-the-global-muslim-population/"},"archivedate":{"wt":"14 December 2015"},"df":{"wt":"dmy-all"},"date":{"wt":"2009-10-07"},"quote":{"wt":"The Pew Forum’s estimate of the Shia population (10-13%) is in keeping with previous estimates, which generally have been in the range of 10-15%."}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBVs"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.pewforum.org/2009/10/07/mapping-the-global-muslim-population/" id="mwBVw">"Mapping the Global Muslim Population"</a>. 7 October 2009. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20151214172939/http://www.pewforum.org/2009/10/07/mapping-the-global-muslim-population/" id="mwBV0">Archived</a> from the original on 14 December 2015<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwBV4">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwBV8">10 December</span> 2014</span>. <q id="mwBWA">The Pew Forum’s estimate of the Shia population (10-13%) is in keeping with previous estimates, which generally have been in the range of 10-15%.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Mapping+the+Global+Muslim+Population&amp;rft.date=2009-10-07&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewforum.org%2F2009%2F10%2F07%2Fmapping-the-global-muslim-population%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AShia+Islam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt19" id="mwBWE"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt19" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwBWI"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-Newman2013-6" id="cite_note-Newman2013-6"><a href="./Shia_Islam#cite_ref-Newman2013_6-0" rel="mw:referen