56"><a href="./Shia_Islam#cite_ref-56" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-56" class="mw-reference-text">Nasr (1979), p. 15</span></li><li about="#cite_note-Imamat-57" id="cite_note-Imamat-57"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Shia_Islam#cite_ref-Imamat_57-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Shia_Islam#cite_ref-Imamat_57-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Imamat-57" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation encyclopaedia" about="#mwt168" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite encyclopedia ","href":"./Template:Cite_encyclopedia"},"params":{"encyclopedia":{"wt":"Encyclopaedia of Islam and the Muslim world; vol.1"},"last":{"wt":"Gleave"},"first":{"wt":"Robert"},"title":{"wt":"Imamate"},"publisher":{"wt":"MacMillan"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-02-865604-5"},"year":{"wt":"2004"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBj8">Gleave, Robert (2004). "Imamate". <i id="mwBkA">Encyclopaedia of Islam and the Muslim world; vol.1</i>. MacMillan. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwBkE">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwBkI"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-02-865604-5" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-02-865604-5" id="mwBkM">978-0-02-865604-5</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Imamate&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopaedia+of+Islam+and+the+Muslim+world%3B+vol.1&amp;rft.pub=MacMillan&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-02-865604-5&amp;rft.aulast=Gleave&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AShia+Islam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt168" id="mwBkQ"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt168" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw