arams":{"author":{"wt":"Saunders, John Joseph"},"title":{"wt":"A History of Medieval Islam"},"publisher":{"wt":"Routledge"},"year":{"wt":"1990"},"page":{"wt":"133"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0415059145"},"quote":{"wt":"Under Mu’izz (955-975) the Fatimids reached the height of their glory, and the universal triumph of isma ‘ilism appeared not far distant. The fourth Fatimid Caliph is an attractive character: humane and generous, simple and just, he was a good administrator, tolerant and conciliatory. Served by one of the greatest generals of the age, Jawhar al-Rumi, a former Greek slave, he took fullest advantage of the growing confusion in the Sunnite world."}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBvY">Saunders, John Joseph (1990). <i id="mwBvc">A History of Medieval Islam</i>. Routledge. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwBvg"> </span>133. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwBvk">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwBvo"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0415059145" title="Special:BookSources/978-0415059145" id="mwBvs">978-0415059145</a>. <q id="mwBvw">Under Mu’izz (955-975) the Fatimids reached the height of their glory, and the universal triumph of isma ‘ilism appeared not far distant. The fourth Fatimid Caliph is an attractive character: humane and generous, simple and just, he was a good administrator, tolerant and conciliatory. Served by one of the greatest generals of the age, Jawhar al-Rumi, a former Greek slave, he took fullest advantage of the growing confusion in the Sunnite world.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+History+of+Medieval+Islam&amp;rft.pages=133&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft.date=1990&amp;rft.isbn=978-0415059145&amp;rft.au=Saunders%2C+John+Joseph&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AShia+Islam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt393" id="mwBv0"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicat